### Vantel: Empowering Commercial Insurance Brokers with AI

**Company Overview:**
- **Name:** Vantel
- **Founded:** 2024
- **Location:** Stockholm, Sweden
- **Team Size:** 2 employees
- **Website:** [vantel.ai](https://vantel.ai)
- **Y Combinator Batch:** W25

**Mission:**
Vantel aims to empower commercial insurance brokers with cutting-edge AI technology, streamlining their workflows and enhancing client service.

**Core Offering:**
Vantel is an AI software platform specifically designed for commercial insurance brokers. It significantly reduces time spent on policy analysis and contract reviews—saving brokers 10+ hours per week. This means less time drowning in PDFs and more time building relationships with clients.

**Why Vantel?**
- Brokers report drastic improvements in efficiency—one customer reclaimed 15 hours weekly and projected a $50,000 increase in annual revenue.
- The platform allows brokers to condense contract review time from hours to mere minutes, making tedious tasks manageable.
- It handles complex documents expertly, allowing users to simply ask questions and get accurate answers without sifting through lengthy texts.

**Client Testimonies:**
- “I used to spend 2 hours per contract review; now it’s just 10 minutes.”
- “Vantel has transformed how I work with 500-page PDFs, letting me ask questions directly.”

**Get Involved:**
Vantel is looking to grow and invites commercial insurance brokers to [Book a Demo](https://vantel.ai/<https:/calendar.app.google/m87RrfwvZxkdbS1aA>) to see how the AI can help scale their brokerage.

**Partnership & Support:**
Vantel is backed by Y Combinator, which lends credibility and access to a network that can help the company thrive in the fintech and insurance spaces.

---

As a startup, Vantel is poised at the intersection of technology and insurance—an area ripe for disruption. With a simple yet powerful AI tool, they’re not just saving time for brokers; they're enabling them to focus on what truly matters: their clients. It’s about empowering people to do their best work, and that’s a mission worth getting behind.
